# Frontend Gap Fixes — ResQLink

Fill all gaps from the ARCHITECTURE.md vs code comparison across dashboard and mobile.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **[firebase_options.dart](file:///d:/gdgsolutions/dashboard/lib/firebase_options.dart) empty fields:** The values for `apiKey`, `appId`, and `messagingSenderId` come from `--dart-define` at build time. This plan adds a **runtime assertion** that crashes with a clear message when they are empty in debug mode. In production builds you must pass the real values via `--dart-define=FIREBASE_WEB_API_KEY=…` etc. — we do NOT hard-code secrets in source.
>
> **Live video feed in dashboard:** The current architecture's "Live Feed tile" will display the camera stream via the incident's `streamUrl` field stored in RTDB. We'll use the [video_player](https://pub.dev/packages/video_player) package already available. If `streamUrl` is empty the tile shows a stylised placeholder — no third-party streaming server is required for the demo.
>
> **Audio capture:** `CameraController` on Android/iOS supports `startAudioOnlyRecording()` → returns an `XFile`. We base64-encode the WAV bytes. This is a stub that makes the code non-empty; full integration with the backend stream upload is the backend team's responsibility.

